course_info.title: Introduction to Artificial Intelligence
course_info.description: A comprehensive introduction to AI for non-technical learners

learning_objectives.tlo: Students will analyze AI concepts, evaluate machine learning applications, and create intelligent solutions for real-world problems.
learning_objectives.elo:
• Identify types of machine learning algorithms
• Explain neural network fundamentals
• Evaluate AI applications across industries
• Analyze ethical implications of AI systems
• Communicate AI concepts to diverse audiences

kdka.knowledge: AI fundamentals, machine learning types, neural networks, ethics
kdka.delivery: Interactive demos, case studies, hands-on AI tools
kdka.context: Real AI applications in healthcare, business, technology
kdka.assessment: AI tool projects, case analysis, ethical discussions

prrr.personal: Career opportunities in AI and tech industry
prrr.relatable: Everyday AI (Siri, Netflix, GPS), social media algorithms
prrr.relative: Progressive understanding from basics to applications
prrr.realworld: Industry case studies, AI tool usage, career pathways

course_modules.title: AI Fundamentals & History
course_modules.objectives: Students will master key concepts in AI fundamentals and apply them practically
course_modules.activities: Interactive sessions, hands-on exercises, case studies related to AI fundamentals
course_modules.assessment: Formative quiz, practical project, peer discussion on AI fundamentals

course_modules.title: Machine Learning Types & Applications
course_modules.objectives: Students will master key concepts in machine learning and apply them practically
course_modules.activities: Interactive sessions, hands-on exercises, case studies related to machine learning
course_modules.assessment: Formative quiz, practical project, peer discussion on machine learning
